Chapter 104: Getting Streaked!

Sophie read the comments scrolling past and felt the familiar sting of discouragement settle in her chest. Even with an Emperor notification, her audience’s default assumption was that nothing good could actually be happening to her. That she wasn’t worth the attention. That it had to be a mistake.

She opened her mouth to thank the visitor anyway, fake or not, the polite thing to do was acknowledge the Emperor status, when the gifts started.

Stan said nothing in the chat. He didn’t type a greeting. He didn’t announce himself. He simply opened his wallet, loaded his account for a full ten minutes without stopping, methodically, patiently, building up a balance large enough to make a statement that would leave no room for doubt, and then began.

SUPER ROCKET × 10

The chat rippled.

SUPER ROCKET × 20

The ripple became a wave.

SUPER ROCKET × 30

The wave became a tsunami.

@BrainJustCrashed: [HOLY MOLLY]

@RealityCheckFailed: [IT’S REAL. IT’S ACTUALLY REAL.]

@KneelPeasants: [MASTER STREAK IS BACK.]

@MathDeletedItself: [Thirty rockets in the first volley. THIRTY. This is not a drill.]

@RentPaidInstantly: [THAT WAS MY ENTIRE YEAR’S SALARY IN 3 SECONDS]

@DoubtDeleted: [I APOLOGIZE FOR EVERYTHING I SAID EARLIER]

@StreamerHeartbeatMonitor: [SHE’S SHAKING SOMEBODY CHECK HER PULSE 😭]

@DoctorInChat: [@StreamerHeartbeatMonitor I am NOT licensed for this level of wealth exposure]

@GiftCalculator9000: [bro just dropped a small car casually]

@MoralSupportOnly: [I CAN’T EVEN AFFORD WIFI AND THIS GUY IS DOING FIREWORKS]

@WhaleSpotted: [NATIONAL GEOGRAPHIC VOICE: the rare streak emerges]

@HistoryChannelReject: [future textbooks: "The Day Chat Lost Its Mind"]

@ChatLagVictim: [MY PHONE FROZE FROM THE PURE WEALTH]

@RespectfullyBroke: [sir... respectfully... hello... I exist too]

@InstantBeliever: [I NEVER DOUBTED HIM (don’t check my previous messages)]

@Shock.exeStopped: [my soul just left and came back with interest]

@CoinRainEnjoyer: [THIS IS BETTER THAN FIREWORKS ON NEW YEAR’S]

@OverstimulatedViewer: [TOO MANY EFFECTS I CAN’T SEE THE STREAMER ANYMORE]

@ScreenshotWarrior: [EVERYONE SCREENSHOT EVERYTHING THIS IS EVIDENCE]

The red gift notifications cascaded down Sophie’s screen like a digital waterfall. The platform-wide announcement, visible in every active stream on TikTuk Live, blazed across millions of screens simultaneously.

[Streak has gifted Super Rocket × 30 in Sophie Youngs’s room.]

Sophie’s hands flew to her mouth.

"Thank you, oh my god, thank you so much, Master Streak—"

Her voice cracked slightly. She was trying to maintain composure and failing beautifully. The camera caught the exact moment her professional streamer face dissolved into genuine, unscripted shock, eyes wide, cheeks flushing, hands pressed together as if in prayer.

"Thank you, Master Streak! Thank you for coming to my stream, I can’t believe—"

She couldn’t finish the sentence. The gift counter was still climbing.

SUPER ROCKET × 50

SUPER ROCKET × 100

The viewer count was now rising so fast the number was blurring, five thousand, ten thousand, twenty thousand, people pouring in from every corner of the platform, abandoning their own streams to witness what was happening in this tiny, previously invisible room.

@MythologyUnlocked: [The legend returns.]

@WarZoneReporter: [Streak just picked a random small streamer and started carpet-bombing her with rockets.]

@AlgorithmProphet: [This girl is about to go from 300 viewers to the front page in under five minutes.]

@I’mjustAgirl: [I love this man. I don’t know who he is but I love him.]

@SirYeetsAlot: [@I’mjustAgirl Of course you would love him, he’s rich after all]

@SuddenDevotion: [I CAN DEFEND THIS MAN IN COURT WITH ZERO CONTEXT]

@PromotionSpeedrun: [she just unlocked fame, God may this luck follow me...]

@ViewerCountWatcher: [300... 800... 2K... BRO IT’S CLIMBING LIKE CRYPTO]

@NewReligionFounder: [we gathering every Friday to honor the whale]

@WhaleEconomics101: [this is not spending money this is redistributing hope]

@ChatAscended: [WE ARE NO LONGER A SMALL STREAM WE HAVE TRANSCENDED]

@StreamerInShock: [SHE SO STUNNED THAT SHE CAN’T EVEN FINISH A SENTENCE 😭]

@FrontPageForecaster: [mods get ready y’all about to be overwhelmed]

@LagFromWealth: [my app is buffering from the sheer financial pressure]

@InstantHistorian: [future me: "I was there when it happened"]

@HeroEntranceMusic: [someone play some boss music like (lie down funk)]

@CoinStormSurvivor: [we didn’t choose this moment this moment chose us]

@NameChangedToFan: [changing my username to StreakFan#847 immediately]

@GratefulBystander: [I don’t benefit from this at all but I feel blessed]

Sophie’s stream, which had been languishing in the platform’s lowest tier for two weeks, was now rocketing toward the top of TikTuk Live’s real-time rankings, carried upward on the back of a gift barrage from the single most famous whale in the platform’s history.

And Stan Harrison lay in a dark apartment with a sleeping woman on his shoulder, phone held casually in one hand, thumb tapping the gift button with the mechanical rhythm of a man who had done this before and intended to do it for quite a while longer.

The night was young. The rebate was waiting. And Sophie Youngs’s streaming career was about to change forever.

Sophie’s viewer count climbed like a rocket chasing its own tail.

Ten thousand. Fifty thousand. A hundred thousand. Two hundred thousand. Three hundred thousand, and still rising, the number ticking upward so fast the display could barely keep pace. Every active user on TikTuk Live who wasn’t already watching had received the platform-wide notification, and curiosity was doing the rest.

@BreakingNewsButMakeItChaotic: [Streak is back. Streak is in some nobody’s room. Streak is gifting again.]

@RealityBuffering: [I CAN’T PROCESS THIS IN REAL TIME]

@SmallStreamHistorian: [this is officially the day everything changed]

@FinancialEarthquakeWatch: [WHY IS HE DOING THIS LIKE IT’S A DAILY ROUTINE 😭]

@RespectfullyConfused: [bro just logs in, causes chaos, refuses to elaborate]

@ChatWitnessProtection: [I was here before the greatness... and I will probably never recover]

@AlgorithmVictim: [her stream is about to get recommended to EVERYONE]

@SleepDeprivedObserver: [I stayed up for memes and now I’m watching history]

@WhaleBehaviorSpecialist: [scientists need to study this man’s targeting system]

@UnexpectedMainCharacter: [she woke up today thinking it was a normal stream 💀]

@ViewerCountRocket: [3k → 8k → 20k... WHAT IS THIS TRAJECTORY]

@ConfusionMaxedOut: [is this generosity or performance art??]

@KeyboardPhilosopher: [what even is money at this point]

@TooLateToLeave: [I tried to close the app but my curiosity won’t let me]

The last time this had happened, Xenia had been a mid-tier streamer with a decent following and an unremarkable trajectory. One night with Streak had turned her into the TikTuk Queen, the most-followed female streamer on the entire platform. The transformation had been so dramatic, so sudden, so thoroughly documented in the platform’s lore that "getting Streaked" had become unofficial slang for overnight success.

And now it was happening again. In real time. To Sophie Youngs.
